#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn about the QMake build system in Spack, a script generator for Qt-based "
"projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:13
msgid "QMake"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:15
msgid ""
"Much like Autotools and CMake, QMake is a build-script generator designed by "
"the developers of Qt. In its simplest form, Spack's ``QMakePackage`` runs "
"the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:18
msgid ""
"$ qmake\n"
"$ make\n"
"$ make check  # optional\n"
"$ make install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:26
msgid ""
"QMake does not appear to have a standardized way of specifying the "
"installation directory, so you may have to set environment variables or edit "
"``*.pro`` files to get things working properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:28
msgid ""
"QMake packages will depend on the virtual ``qmake`` package which is "
"provided by multiple versions of Qt: ``qt`` provides Qt up to Qt5, and ``qt-"
"base`` provides Qt from version Qt6 onwards. This split was motivated by the "
"desire to split the single Qt package into its components to allow for more "
"fine-grained installation. To depend on a specific version, refer to the "
"documentation on :ref:`virtual-dependencies`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:33
msgid "Phases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:35
msgid ""
"The ``QMakeBuilder`` and ``QMakePackage`` base classes come with the "
"following phases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:37
msgid "``qmake`` - generate Makefiles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:38
msgid "``build`` - build the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:39
msgid "``install`` - install the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:41
msgid "By default, these phases run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:43
msgid ""
"$ qmake\n"
"$ make\n"
"$ make install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:50
msgid ""
"Any of these phases can be overridden in your package as necessary. There is "
"also a ``check`` method that looks for a ``check`` target in the Makefile. "
"If a ``check`` target exists and the user runs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:54
msgid "$ spack install --test=root <qmake-package>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:59
msgid "Spack will run ``make check`` after the build phase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:62
msgid "Important files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:64
msgid ""
"Packages that use the QMake build system can be identified by the presence "
"of a ``<project-name>.pro`` file. This file declares things like build "
"instructions and dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:67
msgid "One thing to look for is the ``minQtVersion`` function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:69
msgid "minQtVersion(5, 6, 0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:74
msgid ""
"This means that Qt 5.6.0 is the earliest release that will work. You should "
"specify this in a ``depends_on`` statement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:78
msgid "Build system dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:80
msgid ""
"At the bare minimum, packages that use the QMake build system need a ``qt`` "
"dependency. Since this is always the case, the ``QMakePackage`` base class "
"already contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:83
msgid "depends_on(\"qt\", type=\"build\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:88
msgid ""
"If you want to specify a particular version requirement, or need to link to "
"the ``qt`` libraries, you can override this in your package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:90
msgid "depends_on(\"qt@5.6.0:\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:95
msgid "Passing arguments to qmake"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:97
msgid ""
"If you need to pass any arguments to the ``qmake`` call, you can override "
"the ``qmake_args`` method like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:99
msgid ""
"def qmake_args(self):\n"
"    return [\"-recursive\"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:105
msgid "This method can be used to pass flags as well as variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:108
msgid "``*.pro`` file in a sub-directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:110
msgid ""
"If the ``*.pro`` file used to tell QMake how to build the package is found "
"in a sub-directory, you can tell Spack to run all phases in this sub-"
"directory by adding the following to the package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:112
msgid "build_directory = \"src\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:118
msgid "External documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/qmakepackage.rst:120
msgid ""
"For more information on the QMake build system, see: http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/"
"qmake-manual.html"
msgstr ""
